    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ 425\u00b0F/ Gas 7</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pecan-sage-and-blue-cheese-risotto/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>sweet <span class=\"text-highlight\">potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></span></strong><span class=\"text-highlight\"> (</span>skins on) into\u00a0bite-sized pieces</p> <p>Place the<strong> sweet potato</strong> on a baking tray, drizzle with <span class=\"text-highlight\">1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]\u00a0</span></span><strong>olive oil</strong> and season generously with<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p> <p>Put\u00a0them in the oven for 30 min or until crisp</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pecan-sage-and-blue-cheese-risotto/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>vegetable</strong>\u00a0<strong>stock cube<span style=\"color:#e86754;\">[s]</span></strong>\u00a0with 800ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span>\u00a0<strong>boiled water</strong></p> <p>Peel and dice the<strong>\u00a0brown onion<span style=\"color:#e86754;\">[s]</span></strong>\u00a0finely</p> <p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pecan-sage-and-blue-cheese-risotto/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add <span class=\"text-highlight\">1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span></span><strong> olive oil</strong> to a large pan over a medium heat</p> <p>Once\u00a0hot, add the <strong>diced</strong>\u00a0<strong>onion</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3 min until soft but not coloured</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pecan-sage-and-blue-cheese-risotto/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>arborio</strong>\u00a0<strong>rice</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong>\u00a0<strong>garlic</strong>\u00a0into the softened <strong>onion</strong>\u00a0</p> <p>Add <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>1/3</strong> </span>of the <strong>stock</strong> and stir continuously with a wooden spoon until it's absorbed</p> <p>Continue to add the stock a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 15-20 min, until all the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pecan-sage-and-blue-cheese-risotto/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>pecans</strong> to the sweet potato tray and put it back in the oven for 5 min or until they have slightly darkened in colour</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pecan-sage-and-blue-cheese-risotto/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>sage</strong> finely,\u00a0including the stalks</p> <p>Chop the <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>pecans</strong> coarsely</p> <p>Add the <strong>sage</strong> and <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>3/4</strong></span> of the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>sweet potato</strong> to the risotto</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pecan-sage-and-blue-cheese-risotto/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>cooked</strong></span> <strong>risotto</strong> from the heat and crumble in <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>half</strong></span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [all]</span> the\u00a0<strong>blue cheese </strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">(save the rest for another time)</span>, stirring through until melted</p> <p>Serve in bowls and top with the <strong>remaining sweet potato</strong> and <strong>chopped pecans</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
